description: Enjoying a gorgeous single lifestyle with lots of encounters in the big city! That was Trudy the country girl's reason for coming to New York. To have metropolitan romances with all the men that aren't around in her small town. To keep her from getting into trouble, her friends introduce Linc as a "bodyguard" until she gets used to life in the city. As a playboy who's grown tired of the romantic chase, he's the perfect practice boyfriend who'll make her into a confident, sophisticated cosmopolitan!
name: Vol. 1

description: Yesterday, Walter tried to kill himself. Today, he wakes up to find that everyone who comes near him suddenly and inexplicably dies. Everyone, that is, except for a mysterious lady named Eliza, who is desperately trying to keep Walter safe from a deadly assassin known as Miller - which would be easy if he didn't keep coming back from the dead without a scratch on him. Learn the true meaning of life and death in AFFLICTION.
name: Vol. 1

description: Witness the origin of American Barbarian. The Yoosamon have defended Fortress Lionhorn for as long as anyone can remember. The red-white-and-blue haired warriors have met their match in Two-Tank Omen, an undead pharoah with tanks for feet. They clash in violent battle. Who will live? Who will die?

person_credits.name: Tom Scioli
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description:
Little Orphan Annie is back to fight injustice in the 21st century! She's called Annie now and her adoptive father, Oliver Warbucks (don't call him Daddy), is a buff billionaire in the risk-seeking mold of Elon Musk or Larry Ellison. Sometimes chaperoned by Warbucks' ace flyer Amelia Santiago, Annie and her canine companion Sandy find their way into thrilling and often dangerous adventures.

Volume 1 of the new "Annie" ebook series by comic artist Ted Slampyak and comic book historian and former New York Daily News editor Jay Maeder will feature collected strips from "Annie and the Phantom Commando" and "Annie and the Queen of the Martian Iguanas" story arcs.
name: The Phantom Commando & The Queen of the Martian Iguanas

description: Archie and Betty, Archie and Veronica, Moose and Midge, Chuck and Nancy, Reggie and Midge -- as you can see, the dating scene at Riverdale High School is far from simple! No matter who your favorite couple is, you can't help but laugh at the dysfunctional world of teenage dating! This collection features 128 pages of hand-picked, favorite stories about the romantic ups and downs of Riverdale!
name: TPB

volume.name: Archie Comics Spectacular: It's A Date

description: Halloween eve has finally come and Arizona Goof has organized a big masquerade party! Everyone is excited to witness Arizona's scary tricks, but this party offers something even more astonishing than frightening special effects...!

volume.name: Arizona Goof and the Halloween Party

description: Armageddon is the first soldier of Lucifer and it is his goal to reshape Earth and decimate the entire human population. But Armageddon doesn't realize that the residents of Earth aren't planning to be killed that easily.

The world as we know it is no more. During an unknown outbreak 90% of Earth's population are either dead, or has been transformed into zombified cyborgs. Riley Thompson and his family are trying to stay together and most importantly, stay alive!
name: Blood and Plague

description: Supernatural beings live among humans in peace, yet Jack Crimson finds his life as a werewolf frustrating, and wants nothing more than a cure. Desperate to free himself from this curse, he makes a series of decisions leading him down an unexpected path. Learn more about this mysterious world of vampires, zombies, werewolves, and more starting here in this introductory issue zero!
The free preview of the upcoming series from Imbria Arts.
name: Chapter 0

description: "If you ever set even one foot in my kingdom...I'll take you away and put you in the world's most beautiful cage!" This is a bittersweet memory of Jasmine's ex-lover, Sheikh Tariq. When she visits his desert homeland, he sweeps her away to his rose-colored palace, as promised. She dreams of reconciling her love for him, but will Tariq's heart want her back without knowing why she left him once before?
name: Vol. 1

description: A man running through the streets alone at night, an overheard conversation on a train, a surprising first date, and a discussion between two comic book authors.

Donald Duckling and his friends are trick-or-treating around Quack Town when a daring robbery takes place! Donald is convinced that the thieves are actually monsters, and sets out to prove their secret identity. But he may get more than he bargained for when the fleeing robbers take refuge in Donald's classroom!

volume.name: Donald Duckling and the Halloween Night

description: Waking up with no memories, an odd robot embarks on a quest to gather his lost data. With only an odd, fuzzy companion, J03 finds helpful friends, and dangerous enemies.

In 1947, hard-boiled police detective Tom Fraley was murdered by a vicious serial killer. Now, in 2013, someone is replicating that killer's pattern. Fraley's spirit returns to hunt down the criminal and take vengeance for his own death.
What would you do if you went to Heaven only to be told you couldn't get in? Fight for it! A violent, blasphemous, one-shot comic by Darren Hupke and Jean-Paul Deshong.

The sequel to Zenescope's hit Grimm Fairy Tales spin-off Neverland is now available. Evil has risen again in Neverland and the threat to earth has never been greater. The new ruler of Neverland needs human blood to grow his power and he plans to take his prey from one of the world's biggest cities, New York, by pulling its residents directly into Neverland. And all that stands between him and success of his devious plan is a small group of warriors led by Cross, Tiger Lily and Tinker Belle.
name: TPB

volume.name: Grimm Fairy Tales Presents: Neverland - Hook

description: When the world's smartest and most dangerous man goes rogue, there's only one person who can handle the situation: his damaged and broken predecessor. Meet Spencer Cradle, the second smartest man on the planet. Cradle's objective: hunt down the genetically-altered super-intelligent menace known as John Knowledge. On the battlefields of the 21st Century, it's no longer important to be the strongest or most athletic soldier. You have to be the smartest.
name: Part One: A Fire in the Master's House is Set

description: Lemuria #1 contains two humourous fantasy stories set in this wild world--in one, a sword-slinging barbarian babe raised by lemurs makes a new friend while raiding a temple; in the other, a legendary hero seeks the bravest man in the world, and finds that he's not exactly what he expected.

A forbidden love pushes a small western town to the brink with explosive results, propelling us into an epic story of Action and Adventure, Love and Betrayal, Samurai and Cowboys! Welcome to the world of LITTLE RISING SON!
name: Bloodlines Part 1 of 3

description: President Azuma, known for both his intelligence and attractiveness, fell in love with at first sight with Mizuki Hasegawa. Mizuki Hasegawa wasn't very impressed with his courtship, from the first surprising fumbling he felt on the train on his way to school, to being told that he reminded Azuma of a dog he used to own. Azuma found himself with his hands full as Mizuki battled him every step of the way to no avail, and all too soon, the pair found themselves in the eye of a hurricane of love. Now a long established couple, the pair have matured a bit, and return in this sequel to the wildly popular original series. Everything is far from smooth sailing, however, as their love continues to encounter category 4 storms thanks to Mizuki's short temper and Azuma's own machinations. Can their love survive?
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Love Is Like A Hurricane PLUS

description: A man enamored with the old ways is making chilling sacrifices on the longest and hottest day of the year to bring his old gods back into the modern world. It is up to Lisa and the Macabre Squad to track this madman down and put a stop to him, before the world is destroyed.

One evening while hanging out, Oku confesses to his friend and neighbor, Kanbayashi, that he is not attracted to women at all and thinks that he might be gay. One thing leads to another, and the two find themselves between the sheets sharing a night of passion. From that day on, though, the pair act as if nothing at all happened. Kan goes on to date a string of women while Oku begins seeing several different men. Three years on, things come to a head during Christmas break, with secrets laid bare between them. Where will things go from there? Two university students explore love, sexuality and friendship in this gentle coming of age tale.
name: Vol. 1

description: Sub-Par City's finest are hot on the trail of two scaly scalawags and none of them are too happy to be missing their beloved Squires play in Game 7!

A hand-drawn, beautifully colored book from the creator of Dragon and Goat and the web-comic Cloud Arcadia, The Panopticorn tells the story of a farmer in Southern Illinois who discovers a new seed that may save his small farm or plot sinister harvest of its own.
name: GN

description: Vera Greentea presents a Father's Day comic book collection of dark fantasy stories. Each of the three tales focus on a decision made by a father - regarding, or sometimes ignoring his child - and the consequences on that child, and the rest of us. With art by Lizzy John, Joseph Lacroix and Ben Jelter, PAPA blends evocative storytelling with haunting images to create deeply frightening worlds.

Plagued is the true story of a fake apocalypse. On one terrifying night in post-tsunami Thailand, all signs point to the inevitable end of Ryan Estrada's life, if not the world. A harrowing tale of locusts, frogs and hitler cats.

volume.name: Plagued: The True Story of A Fake Apocalypse

description: Long before Human+ soldiers in the Gaal Defense Force make Terra Force One status, they are trained in the rigorous Program. This is the story of six recruits who are going through The Program; they have many powers and they will be tested as a team against many evils, seen and unseen.

The McConnells are a down-on-their-luck family desperately in need of a fresh start and a lucky break. When Becky is sucked into a cycle of recurring dreams filled with monstrously burned and disfigured people, her world unravels and her dreams start to become a nightmarish reality.

Private Investigator J. Parker Wrighte is hired by Monolith Studios to look into the suicide of one of their major stars, Pepper O'Dell. He discovers from talking to her co-star, Jack B. Nimbeau, that Pepper was not the sweet and innocent girl next she played on the screen. Parker also meets the seductive screen star Domino Mueller and drives with her to a clinic run by Dr. Rome.

volume.name: Retrowood: All Roads Lead To Rome

description: Dave Willis is a down and out baseball scout who was once a Major League pitcher loved by fans the world over. Now, an ignored has-been on his last leg, Dave jets to Israel after seeing news footage of a Palestinian teen throwing rocks with a speed and accuracy that defies even the best pitchers on most Major League Baseball teams. Does it really matter he's throwing them at Israeli soldiers? This new potential pitching discovery could redeem Dave in the eyes of his peers. But when the former athlete finds himself in the middle of a decades old conflict, will he fail in his mission before having a chance to even succeed?

Scrooge gets a new kind of prank call when his old enemy Magica De Spell uses a haunted cell phone to brainwash him into doing her bidding. His bank vault emptying, but Scrooge doesn't realize that Magica is leading him to the poorhouse! Can Donald and the nephews untangle the haunted cell phone mystery before Uncle Scrooge ends up bankrupt?

volume.name: Scrooge McDuck and the Haunted Cellphone

description: Huey, Dewey and Louie want to trick Uncle Scrooge to earn their Halloween candy, like they try to do every year! To succeed, they'll have to deal with Scrooge's new security system first. But their tinkering causes some hilarious side effects when Scrooge confuses all of his friends for his nemesis, Magica De Spell!

volume.name: Scrooge McDuck and the Very Special Halloween

description: Magica De Spell has stolen Uncle Scrooge's Number-One Dime! But when he tries to get it back, it gets lost in another dimension! Will Uncle Scrooge and Magica De Spell be able to work together to retrieve Scrooge's most prized possession?

volume.name: Scrooge McDuck and the Witchy Business

description:
Collects Mega Man #24, Sonic Universe #51, Sonic the Hedgehog #248, and Mega Man #25:

The year's most talked-about comic crossover is HERE, collected for the first time in graphic novel form! SONIC/MEGA MAN: WORLDS COLLIDE BOOK 1 collects the historic first meeting of two of the biggest video game icons in the world! See the two blue heroes do battle while their evil counterparts doctors Eggman and Wily revel in every minute of it! Featuring all the action, fun and adventure of the first four chapters of the 12-part miniseries, plus exclusive bonus features you can only see in this graphic novel collection!
name: Kindred Spirits

description: Arcana Comics and SteamPunk Originals collects the first four chapters onf an epic SteamPunk Future set in the world of Oz. A century after the witch is killed, the Emerald City is ruled by a once-revived hero, and salvation comes from the unlikely wrench of young Victoria Wright. She comes to find out the smallest of actions can have much larger implications, and the most insignificant of us can change the world. Rediscover old friends and new heroes along the way, and learn how something that was once a gift... Can turn into a curse.
name: Vol. 1

description: The first book in the series, this introduces the character who will appear in each of the books, although he may not always be the MAIN character in the books.
A silent short story about Ardee the Acrobat: the mechanical boy who dreams of running away from the Circus... to become an accountant.

Chapter 1: "A Thief in the Night"

Meet notorious thief and seducer Tristan Casimir, a young adventurer who is unknowingly thrust towards his destiny to unite a kingdom, save his true love and become a hero.

Who is the mysterious girl that attacks Tristan? What does the treacherous Lord Orfio have in store? Who is brave enough to wage war against the Sapphire Kingdom?

Find out in this over-sized debut issue - welcome to the long forgotten world of The Thief, where adventure, danger and romance await.

Be Prepared!
name: A Thief in the Night

description:
Catalina Jones is a mild-mannered probabilistic risk assessor.

Her life was relatively normal; she had a fianc , a cat, and one big jerk of a boss. But now, thanks to the fallout from a bizarre microwave burrito/graviton missile accident, she also has the power to control probability itself. This new power is wild, thus far unpredictable, and potentially deadly. With the help of her friend Xi Chen she must learn to control her abilities before she destroys her whole neighborhood-or worse, the universe-and attracts too much attention from the creepy guys in dark suits.

Collects To The Power Against chapters 1-6.
name: Vol. 1

description: "Tribute" comic books tells the stories of the classic entertainers that have passed on. Honoring these icons who have made a difference in the in film as well as the world in this unique format. This collected edition features Elizabeth Taylor, Marilyn Monroe, James Dean and Frank Capra.
name: GN

description:
Book 1- Three orphan Monks are sent on a mission to recover a valuable artifact, when one of them is kidnapped by the mysterious bird-like creatures known only as the Storm Reavers, During the epic Kung-Fu battle that ensues, the artifact is smashed open, unleashing a mysterious curse upon their leader Mao, who is torn to shreds by the blast.

With strange new abilities and a determination to rescue their friend, they must set out to confront the Storm Reavers in their homeland. But first they must face the wrath of the Elders of their Monastery for their failure to complete their mission.
name: The Shadow King

description:
A Post Apocalyptic Anthology. Three comics creators, three stories, one theme.

THE COURIER IN RED - by Mark Penman

THE WOMAN IN THE WASTES - by James Lawrence

NO EXIT - by Andrew Tunney

Based off the best selling novel by William Shatner, The TekWar Chronicles. Finally collected into one edition, of the epic futuristic adventure, based on William Shatner's best-selling TekWar novel series! After spending 4 years in cryogenic stasis for crimes he is certain he did not commit, Jake Cardigan is mysteriously released. Finding himself lost in a world that has changed since his incarceration, Jake tries to put his life back together. His wife and son are gone, or in hiding, and Jake fights the strong urge to self-medicate using a digital drug called Tek. Offered a job to locate a missing enigmatic scientist, Jake can already feel the puppet strings manipulating him to return to the life that got him jailed in the first place. And his troubles are only beginning. With never before seen images and a foreword by William Shatner.
name: TPB

volume.name: William Shatner The Tek War Chronicles Omnibus
Firefighter! Daigo of Fire Company M

deck: Ginger and Elvis set off to Africa to rescue a dinosuar while Colonel Dachsund, a big game hunter, is bent on eating sasquatch.
description: Collects issues #6-9
name: Book 2

description:
A new direction in the FATHOM Universe begins! Aspen Matthews attempts to return to a normal life with her fellow humans after turning down the Blue's pleas for help. However, the ice queen Vana and her deadly minions step up their machinations with a devastating attack on the surface world. Yet, the biggest surprise may be the return of one of Fathom's most instrumental characters--and someone that shares a painful past with Aspen! Writer David Wohl, artist Alex Konat and colorist Beth Sotelo team up once again to bring you the latest adventures of Michael Turner's most beloved creation!

Note: The digital edition (10/23/2013) for this issue was released a week before the print edition (10/30/2013).

List of covers and their creators:

name: Stranger In A Strange Land

description: The final issue of Family Pets is here! Thomasina must come to terms with her loss while she makes a hard choice in order to save the people she loves most.

From the New York Times best selling novel, Meghan Chase's true identity has been revealed. She is the daughter of King Oberon. Half-fey, she is more determined than ever to escape from the Seelie Court to continue her search for her stolen brother, Ethan - even if it means facing off against the handsome and deadly Prince Ash.

Turns out blowing the whistle aginst your former employer -- the US government -- may not be the healthiest move after all for the disgraced ex-superhero known as The Liberator. Bluewater Comics' LOU FERRIGNO: LIBERATOR #2 concludes the thrilling story of the once idolized icon of America -- the manufactured superhero called the Liberator -- who risks everything to finally really fight for truth and justice. Featuring Lou Ferrigno (The Incredible Hulk,) Michael Dorn (Worf from Star Trek,) Peta Wilson (La Femme Nikita) and Ed Asner (Up.)

NEW RED CIRCLE SERIES! From the world of the New Crusaders, comes the FANTASTIC debut of the high-flying FOX! Emmy Award winning writer/artist Dean Haspiel (Billy Dogma, HBO's Bored to Death) and Eisner Award winning writer Mark Waid (Daredevil, Thrillbent) bring the legendary, pulp-style hero The Fox to life in Freak Magnet, Part One: The True Face of MyFace! When photojournalist Paul Patton, Jr. donned a super hero costume, he thought it would be a quick way to make some newsnow the strange and unusual just can't help but be drawn to the freak-magnetism of the fabulous fighting FOX! While working on a puff-piece at the Red Circle Gazette, an evil truth about social media mogul Lucy Fur is discovered, bringing Paul face-to-face with a criminal kingpin! Get in on the ground floor with the hottest new fall series featuring art and story from the biggest names in comics today! Get freaky!

Double the action in this special edition of the "Lou Ferrigno: Liberator". Featuring both issues of the awards winning mini series. Ed Migliocetti (Lou Ferrigno) has served his country. When the endless war began, he put aside his football career to sign up for the military. And when the powers-that-be drafted him into the Enhanced Abilities Initiative, he became known as The Liberator. Teamed with a group of supers Sidewinder, Gaia and Volt Liberator represented the best of America. Or so he thought. He soon found himself doing the governments dirty work assassinations, regime change, infrastructure sabotage. Through it all, Ed followed orders. He was a good soldier. Featuring Lou Ferrigno (The Incredible Hulk,) Michael Dorn (Worf from Star Trek,) Peta Wilson (La Femme Nikita) and Ed Asner (Up.)

With the announcement of their impending nuptials, Prince William and Kate Middleton have captured the public imagination in much the same way the William's parents did a generation ago. Now Bluewater Productions is publishing a behind-the-curtain look at the royal couple a new biography comic book.

Spider-Man goes hunting... for a Vulture!

By Dan Slott and Ryan Stegman.

Also: The Superior Spider-Man joins forces with the X-Men!

By Christopher Yost and Paco Medina.

Collects:

  • Superior Spider-Man #3
  • Avenging Spider-Man #16
  • Spider-Man Noir: Eyes Without A Face #2.
